Types of Testing- Unit Tests- Integration Tests - End To End Tests - One "end" is the user, the other is all the stuff on the other side of our application (services, services use databases, all that jazz) "End to End Testing"Unit Testing - Testing individual "units" of code in isolation from all their dependencies - a "unit" is usually a function or a method on a class. -Unit tests by definition: - Cannot touch the network, the file system, or databases, etc.Integration Tests: - Anytime we test more than one unit together. - Component tests in Angular - "TestBed" is an integration testing tool from angular for testing components, services, all that stuff outside the context of a running angular application"Isolated Integration Tests" - automate the user experience of the application "Developer End-To-End Tests" - We are writing tests that verify our understanding and implementation of business requirements. - Everything that the application communicates with outside of my application - APIs, etc. - I FAKE those. "Real End to End Tests"
